      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get what you're saying about pattern recognition but that doesn't explain why the \"signal\" feels so synchronized. if science says it's all just gas and dust, then how do you explain the fact that we havent actually mapped every single millimeter of that sector with 100% certainty yet? if someone wanted to hide a massive, ancient satellite array in plain sight using stellar masking, wouldn't that be the perfect cover? wouldn't it just look like stars to an astronomer?",
